page.title: 11NATURE CONSERVATION
page.content: Next to our school, there used to be an old railway cutting of the {Edgware-Highgate}and{London}Railway (1867-1964).It is now disused and we are converting the track into a nature reserve. We've been lashing down brambles and cutting back trees. There's still one old railway carriage on it's side.All of this is an example of how man changes the landscape and its plants and animals. Walking long the{Dollis Nature {Reserve}one sees a variety of plant growth....... {TREE GROWTH The {Birch }and {Oak}are two of the most common trees in the nature reserve.
